# Prep rain data for non-point source (NPS) ungaged load estimates

Prep rain data for non-point source (NPS) ungaged load estimates

## Usage

``` r
util_nps_preprain(rain, yrrng = NULL)
```

## Arguments

- rain:

  data frame of rainfall data, see
  [`rain`](https://tbep-tech.github.io/tbeploads/reference/rain.md)

- yrrng:

  numeric vector of a single year or a two year range to filter the
  data, defaults to NULL (no filtering)

## Value

A data frame of monthly total rainfall (inches) by drainage basin

## Details

The inverse distance weighting scheme of the drainage basin to the rain
gauge is used (with
[`nps_distance`](https://tbep-tech.github.io/tbeploads/reference/nps_distance.md))
to estimate a cumulative monthly total rainfall, including lags of one
and two months.
